Li & Fung Buys Five Companies to Expand Trading, Distribution

-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 
2011-06-22T05:15:36Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-22/li-fung-buys-five-companies-to-expand-trading-distribution.html
Li & Fung Ltd. (494) , the world’s biggest
supplier of clothes and toys to retailers including  Wal-Mart
Stores Inc. (WMT) , acquired five companies to expand its trading and
distribution businesses.  The acquired companies had sales of $660 million and
profit of $80 million last year, the Hong Kong-based company
said in an e-mailed statement today. It didn’t say how much it
paid for the purchases, which were made since March 24.  The acquisitions were made at a price-to-earnings ratio of
about 6.5 times, Chief Executive Officer Bruce Rockowitz said
at an analysts’ briefing, declining to be more specific.  Li & Fung bought TVMania, a European supplier of branded
products whose character licenses include Hello Kitty,  Mickey
Mouse  and Batman and Ben 10, according to the statement. It
also acquired Hampshire Designers, the women’s division of
 Hampshire Group Ltd. (HAMP)   The three other companies are clothing supplier Loyaltex
Apparel, color cosmetics maker Collection 2000 and Thailand-
based furniture trading company Exim Designs.  --Michael Wei and Frank Longid. Editors: Frank Longid,  To contact Bloomberg News staff for this story:
